ellung, dass Muslim_innen das Errungene bedrohen. In diesem Mythos repräsentieren muslimische Andere eine überwunden geglaubte Vergangenheit. Ihre Abwertung im Namen der Emanzipation entpuppt sich als historizistischer Rassismus.  afunded by transcript: Open Library 2019 (Politik)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aIslamophobiazAustria. 0aSocial sciences. 4aHegemonie. 4aIslam. 4aIslamophobie. 4aIslamwissenschaft. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aPolitische Soziologie. 4aPolitische Theorie. 4aÖsterreich. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aAustria.  aHegemony.  aIslam.  aIslamic Studies.  aIslamophobia.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitical Sociology.  aPolitical Theory.  aPolitics.2 atranscript: Open Library 2019 (Politik)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2019 Part 2z978311076669108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW0 cprintz978383764982640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839449820?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839449820zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839449820/original  a978-3-11-071956-7 DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-076669-1 DG Plus PP Package 2019 Part 2b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DSW